## Layout Principles
- **12-column grid** system for responsive layouts
- **Container padding:** 16px (mobile), 24px (tablet), 32px (desktop)
- **Vertical rhythm:** Use 8px multiples for vertical spacing
- **Horizontal alignment:** Left-align text, center-align hero content
- **Touch targets:** Minimum 44x44px

## Animation Guidelines
- **Timing:** 150ms (fast), 200ms (standard), 300ms (slow)
- **Easing:** cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 0.2, 1) - Standard animations
- **Properties:** Always animate transform and opacity, avoid layout properties
- **Use native driver:** Enable for better performance

## Dark Mode Support
- Implement theme switching with useColorScheme hook
- Use semantic color names
- Test contrast ratios in both modes
- Provide smooth transitions between themes

## Responsive Design
- Use Dimensions API for screen sizes
- Breakpoints: mobile (< 768px), tablet (768px - 1024px), desktop (> 1024px)
- Flexible layouts with flexbox
- Adaptive spacing and typography

## StyleSheet Best Practices
- Use StyleSheet.create for performance
- Group related styles together
- Use descriptive names
- Avoid inline styles
- Extract common styles into theme

## Icon Usage
- **Sizes:** xs (16px), sm (20px), md (24px), lg (32px), xl (40px)
- **Colors:** Primary, secondary, muted, success/error states
- **Consistency:** Use consistent icon set throughout app

## Accessibility Styling
- **Contrast ratios:** 4.5:1 minimum for normal text
- **Touch targets:** Minimum 44x44px
- **Focus states:** Visible focus indicators
- **Color alone:** Don't rely on color alone for information

## Performance Optimization
- Optimize image sizes and formats
- Use conditional rendering for complex layouts
- Minimize style recalculations
- Use shouldComponentUpdate for complex components
- Profile performance with Flipper

## Platform-Specific Styling
- Use Platform.select() for iOS/Android differences
- Handle status bar and safe area correctly
- Platform-specific shadows and effects
- Different typography rendering

## Design Token Management
- Centralize design tokens in theme files
- Use semantic naming conventions
- Maintain consistent spacing and typography
- Version control design system changes